<div id="ta28_1" class="block" style="display:block"><ul>
	<li>
	LvS activity: In the LvS environment, by the term &quot;activity&quot; we refer to the folder created through LvS containing one multimedia file, one subtitle file and one or more office file. In this tutorial it is also referred to as &quot;Activity folder&quot;.
	</li>
	<li> Packed activity:An activity in a compressed form, appearing as one file with the extension .lvs.
	</li>
	<li> Areas:</li>
	<ul>
		<li>Multimedia player area: Upper left corner<br />
		</li>
		<li>Document viewer area: Upper right corner<br />
		</li>
		<li>Subtitle editor area: Lower left corner<br />
		</li>
		<li>Notes area: Lower right corner. The notes area is divided in the general comments area (top) and an area for comments per subtitle (bottom). </li>
	</ul>
	<li>Activity element: A file previously prepared for use as part of an LvS activity. It can be a multimedia file (.avi, .mpeg, .wmv, etc.) a subtitle file (.srt, .tts, etc.), an office file (.ppt, .rtf, .doc, .xls, .htm)</li>
	<li>Authoring mode: By activating authoring mode (Options &gt; Authoring mode) all LvS options are available to the user. If authoring mode is deselected, the functions not necessary for the students doing the activity are disabled: </li>
	<ul>
		<li>Set start time, Set end time, Add subtitle and Remove subtitle buttons are hidden.<br />
		</li>
		<li>The End time column is hidden.</li>
		<li>The user cannot edit Teacher&#39;s comments.<br />
		If the activity the author has designed requires the use of the above functions, the students may be asked to enable &quot;authoring mode&quot;.  </li>
	</ul>
</ul>
